Enum ChangeType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ChangeType>
      • org.biopax.paxtools.io.sif.level3.ChangeType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ChangeType>

    public enum ChangeType
extends Enum<ChangeType>
    This enum handles types of modifications and contains utility methods for extracting them.

      • getDeltaFeatures

        public static Map<EntityFeature,ChangeType> getDeltaFeatures(PhysicalEntity left,
                                                             PhysicalEntity right,
                                                             PhysicalEntity leftRoot,
                                                             PhysicalEntity rightRoot)
        This method returns the features that are "changed" between the left and right physical entities. IF these are "contained" in another PE such as a complex or generic it also considers changes to those containers .
        Parameters:
        left - a simple physical entity to be compared.
        right - a simple physical entity to be compared
        leftRoot - if left is in a complex or represented as a generic actual participating entity that contains or subsumes left.
        rightRoot - if right is in a complex or represented as a generic actual participating entity that contains or subsumes right.
        Returns:
        A Map of features of spe, annotated with a change type, direction is from-left-to-right.
